{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "source": [
    "# SOS Multiple Language Example\n",
    "Script of Scripts (SOS) enables multiple languages (matlab, python, etc) to be used in a single jupyter notebook. \n",
    "\n",
    "[running SOS](https://vatlab.github.io/sos-docs/running.html#content)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Installation\n",
    "To install for jupyter notebook:\n",
    "```\n",
    "pip3 install sos\n",
    "pip3 install sos-notebook\n",
    "python3 -m sos_notebook.install\n",
    "```\n",
    "To install jupyterLab extension (note that this transient-display-data only supported for jupyterLab 1.0.0 alpha so it may be best to wait for the 1.0.0 releast to install. However SOS still currently works for notebooks in jupyterLab). \n",
    "```\n",
    "jupyter labextension install transient-display-data\n",
    "jupyter labextension install jupyterlab-sos\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "In a SOS notebook, the dropdown menu on the right side of each block is used to set the language kernel."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Python in SOS\n",
    "Python3 will be installed by default"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 194,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "hello world\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"hello world\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Octave in SOS\n",
    "Once Octave and SOS are installed, install the SOS Octave extension:\n",
    "```\n",
    "pip install sos-matlab\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 195,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "hello world\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "disp(\"hello world\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Putting It All Together\n",
    "\n",
    "Lets generate a complex baseband chirp:\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    s(t) &= \\exp{(j\\pi \\frac{BW}{T} t^2)}\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "\n",
    "in octave and plot it in python using SOS to share data between kernels."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Sharing variables between kernels\n",
    "Using [SOS magic keywords](https://vatlab.github.io/sos-docs/doc/documentation/SoS_Magics.html#put), variables can be shared between kernels. This is still a little buggy but should improve with future versions of JupyterLab.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Octave Block\n",
    "Generate a vector with Matlab/Octave in an octave block:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "% Octave/Matlab code\n",
    "fs = 100e6;\n",
    "N = 1280;\n",
    "bw = 20e6;\n",
    "\n",
    "n = [0:(N-1)]-N/2;\n",
    "t = n/fs;\n",
    "\n",
    "s = exp(1i*pi*.5*(bw/t(end))*(t.^2));\n",
    "\n",
    "figure; hold on;\n",
    "plot(t*1e6,real(s)); plot(t*1e6,imag(s));\n",
    "title('chirp'); xlabel('time (us)'); legend('I','Q'); xlim(1e6*[t(1),t(end)]);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "Plots in octave look bad. Lets try plotting with python instead by passing the data with SOS"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "% vector parsing is still buggy, so let's help out SOS a little bit by passing as a string\n",
    "s = [real(s);imag(s)];\n",
    "s = s(:).';\n",
    "s = sprintf('%i + %ij,' , s);\n",
    "s = ['[',s(1:end-1),']'];\n",
    "\n",
    "t = sprintf('%g,' , t);\n",
    "t = ['[',t(1:end-1),']'];"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "Export vectors from an octave block using the `%put` magic:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%put s t"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "Octave"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### SOS Block\n",
    "In an SOS block, share variables between kernels using the `%get` magic:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "SoS"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%get s t --from Octave\n",
    "s = s\n",
    "t = t"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "SoS"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Python Block\n",
    "Now in a python3 block use the `%expand` magic to load vectors from octave and plot with python:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "kernel": "python3"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%expand\n",
    "\n",
    "# Python code\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "# Note the curly braces which indicate a shared SOS variable\n",
    "s = np.array({s});\n",
    "t = np.array({t});\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure;\n",
    "plt.plot(t*1e6,np.real(s),label='I');\n",
    "plt.plot(t*1e6,np.imag(s),label='Q');\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"time (us)\"); plt.title('Chirp generated by octave'); plt.legend();\n",
    "plt.autoscale(enable=True, axis='x', tight=True);"
   ]
  }
 ],
